HEADWORD: Faded
<hw>Fad"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>That has lost
freshness, color, or brightness; grown dim.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧His
<xex>faded</xex> cheek.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where the <qex>faded</qex> moon⟦br⟧
Made a dim silver twilight.</q> <rj><qau>Keats.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fadedly</ent>⟦br⟧
